MA","target":"recwxW741zdzz3BY5","label":"mentions"},{"source":"rec9qiynXVMVAywMA","target":"recb9w4YLTsZLvXVq","label":"mentions"},{"source":"rec9qiynXVMVAywMA","target":"recP6fsKEckt8QTDh","label":"mentions"},{"source":"rec9qiynXVMVAywMA","target":"rec3qiPi8JN2h86Mj","label":"mentions"},{"source":"rec9qiynXVMVAywMA","target":"recA0rj3f1qQ4llUP","label":"mentions"},{"source":"rec9qiynXVMVAywMA","target":"recfIiRGzMa3c6Kv6","label":"mentions"},{"source":"rec9qiynXVMVAywMA","target":"rec81f3wE4gATsRRE","label":"mentions"},{"source":"rec9qiynXVMVAywMA","target":"recJSfVnIcPibY6aX","label":"mentions"},{"source":"rec9qiynXVMVAywMA","target":"recynQnhWEkUNUZRU","label":"mentions"},{"source":"rec9qiynXVMVAywMA","target":"recL1WV82pXaRBQ59","label":"mentions"},{"source":"rec9qiynXVMVAywMA","target":"reczPjeq0UdahiRrn","label":"mentions"},{"source":"rec9qiynXVMVAywMA","target":"rec0jxSkEigFIdFqj","label":"mentions"},{"source":"rec9qiynXVMVAywMA","target":"recZWekS06dZsVfgD","label":"mentions"},{"source":"rec9qiynXVMVAywMA","target":"recOVVrn4ss5k4zG9","label":"mentions"},{"source":"rec9qiynXVMVAywMA","target":"recTdeFWjvLAXs0t3","label":"mentions"},{"source":"rec9qiynXVMVAywMA","target":"recAiaG6JoV8gdChq","label":"mentions"}],"verses":[{"id":"rec0L5HFTKdyG769S","ref":"1Chr.11.1","text":"Then all Israel gathered themselves to David unto Hebron, saying, Behold, we are thy bone and thy flesh.","year":-1048},{"id":"recx56Bsu0fFJwomV","ref":"1Chr.11.2","text":"And moreover in time past, even when Saul was king, thou wast he that leddest out and broughtest in Israel: and the LORD thy God said unto thee, Thou shalt feed my people Israel, and thou shalt be ruler over my people Israel.","year":-1048},{"id":"recH4XiMmEzwwNjKQ","ref":"1Chr.11.3","text":"Therefore came all the elders of Israel to the king to Hebron; and David made a covenant with them in Hebron before the LORD; and they anointed David king over Israel, according to the word of the LORD by Samuel.","year":-1048},{"id":"recEoi95LbA6QzO8n","ref":"1Chr.11.4","text":"And David and all Israel went to Jerusalem, which is Jebus; where the Jebusites were, the inhabitants of the land.","year":-1048},{"id":"recyF8LfbEL71fOfK","ref":"1Chr.11.5","text":"And the inhabitants of Jebus said to David, Thou shalt not come hither. Nevertheless David took the castle of Zion, which is the city of David.","year":-1048},{"id":"recT3Wz6CL3bKdYOP","ref":"1Chr.11.6","text":"And David said, Whosoever smiteth the Jebusites first shall be chief and captain. So Joab the son of Zeruiah went first up, and was chief.","year":-1048},{"id":"rec0NlIHjmUtMYm45","ref":"1Chr.11.7","text":"And David dwelt in the castle; therefore they called it the city of David.","year":-1048},{"id":"recjRmhjvLyeHVRoU","ref":"1Chr.11.8","text":"And he built the city round about, even from Millo round about: and Joab repaired the rest of the city.","year":-1048}]}
